feat(result): apply Apple HIG / Liquid Glass design

Visible visual change at last — result page now uses the design tokens
imported in main.css (which were sitting unused because result.html
still pointed at the legacy pages/result.css).

What changed visually:
- Background: Apple gray #f5f5f7 (light) / pure black (dark)
- Sticky topbar with backdrop-filter blur(20px) + saturate(180%)
- Score circle: 200-240px, radial gradient with soft accent glow shadow
- Stats grid: hover-lift cards with subtle border, no flat soft bg
- Review items: 18px radius, hover accent border, staggered reveal animation
- Pill status badges with soft background + colored border ring
- Typography: SF Pro / Inter with -0.015em letter-spacing (Apple feel)
- Auto dark mode via prefers-color-scheme
- Honors prefers-reduced-motion (disables stagger + spinner)

Code changes:
- public/result.html — rewrote markup to use new classes:
  result-page, result-topbar, result-hero, result-breakdown.
  Removed link to public/css/pages/result.css legacy.
  Semantic HTML (header, main, footer, sections with aria-label).
  Used `hidden` attribute on AI grading banner.
- public/js/pages/result/summary.js — score color via
  CSS classes (.score-high/.score-mid/.score-low) instead of
  inline style.color. Tokens flow correctly into both themes.

Cleanup:
- Removed public/css/pages/result.css (legacy, replaced by _result.css)
- Removed public/result.legacy.html (old backup)
- Removed scripts/smoke-test-result.js (replaced by .mjs version)
- Removed orphan demo HTML files in public/

Verified:
- Smoke test smoke-test-result.mjs: 9/9 PASS, 0 errors
- Visual capture (Puppeteer) for both light + dark themes
  (artifacts/result_apple_hig_*.png in conversation brain dir)

Files: scripts/capture-visuals.mjs is a new helper for future
       visual regression captures.
